Unicode Reference - Japanese Characters
=======================================

Compiled from Unicode tables (e.g. https://www.compart.com/en/unicode) based on
information from the following sources:

* http://www.unicode.org/charts/
* https://stackoverflow.com/questions/19899554/unicode-range-for-japanese
* http://www.rikai.com/library/kanjitables/kanji_codes.unicode.shtml
* http://www.localizingjapan.com/blog/2012/01/20/regular-expressions-for-japanese-text/

This is not a full list of characters. A lot of archaic and historic symbols are
not included here. The general criteria for inclusion is that the character is 
renderable using common fonts and/or has at list some google hits.
